SIMPLE: muscoid
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Muscoid
<hw>Mus"coid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Muscus</ets> +
<ets>-oid</ets>: cf. F. <ets>muscoide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Mosslike; resembling moss.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muscoid</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Muscoid
<hw>Mus"coid</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A term formerly
applied to any mosslike flowerless plant, with a distinct stem, and
often with leaves, but without any vascular system.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muscoidea</ent>⟦br⟧
